claim.claim-text:
A film formation method comprising the steps of:
preparing a substrate such that a vapor deposition surface of the substrate faces an interior of a film formation chamber;
providing a magnet for a back surface of the substrate;
placing SiO on a crucible disposed in the film formation chamber;
irradiating the SiO with plasma by a plasma generating device to evaporate SiO;
defining a plasma confining space on a side of the vapor deposition surface of the substrate by a magnetic field of the magnet; and
forming SiO2 by causing reaction of the evaporated SiO with plasma in the plasma confining space and activating SiO, and thus forming an SiO2 film over the vapor deposition surface of the substrate without using oxygen as a reaction gas.
